The paper proposes a framework based on deep reinforcement learning to optimize customer service request routing, which involves multiple communication channels. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of customer service log data, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-off between resources and customer satisfaction, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
